claims:
1. A method for detecting a jointly encoded signal received over a multi-path channel comprising: 
receiving a jointly encoded signal over a multi-path channel by N receive antennas, wherein N is an integer greater than one; 
for each of the N receive antennas, sampling the received signal within a chip interval to resolve an antenna-wise chip vector for each of the N receive antennas; 
filtering a block of antenna-wise chip vectors, the block comprising each of the N antenna-wise chip vectors, using a channel quality indicator CQI that describes a multi-path channel over which the jointly encoded signal was received; 
downconverting the filtered block to one of bits and symbols; 
detecting in parallel, for each spreading code by which the jointly encoded signal is spread, the downconverted bits or symbols.

4. The method of claim 1 wherein the SNR is a generalized signal to noise ratio GSNR for one user such that 

\({{GSNR}_{k}\hat{=}{\beta_{k}\frac{{Trace}\left( {\sigma_{d}^{2}{\overset{\_}{I}}_{M}} \right)}{{Trace}\left( {{\overset{\_}{R}}_{zz}\left( {\overset{\_}{W}}_{LMMSE} \right)} \right)}}};\)

where 
βk is a scalar factor that translates a chip-level SNR to a symbol-level SNR for the user; 
σd2 is noise variance with respect to a transmitted chip; 
{overscore (I)}M is an identity matrix of size M×M, wherein M is a number of transmit antennas from which the encoded signal was sent; 
{overscore (R)}zz is an error covariance matrix; and 
{overscore (W)}LMMSE is the filtered block of chip-wise signal vectors.

