31 . A transmitter comprising: 
an encoder for jointly encoding an input signal into a set of at least one symbol that spans a chip; 
a modulator for modulating the set of at least one symbol onto a carrier wave; 
a spreader having an input coupled to an output of the encoder and the modulator for spreading the set of at least one symbol according to a series of spreading codes; 
M antennas for transmitting the set of at least one symbol over a multi-path wireless channel; and 
a processor having an input coupled to a wireless feedback channel and an output coupled to at least one of the encoder and the modulator, said processor responsive to a channel quality feedback to cause at least one of the encoder to change an encoding rate and the modulator to change a modulation.

34. A receiver comprising: 
at least two wireless signal reception means; 
a bank of linear filtering means having a first input coupled to an output of each wireless signal reception means and a second input, said bank of linear filtering means for equalizing signal vectors received over sub-channels of a multipath channel into signal vectors of a single channel; 
channel estimating means having an input coupled to an output of each receive antenna and an output coupled to the second input of the bank of linear filtering means; 
a plurality of joint detection means in parallel with one another, each joint detection means having an input coupled to an output of the bank of linear filtering means and an output coupled to a decoding means, each joint detection means for detecting one of bits or symbols according to one spreading code; 
a chip-to-symbol down-converter, a de-scrambler, and a de-spreader, each disposed between the bank of linear filtering means and the plurality of joint detection means.

35. A transmitter comprising: 
encoding means for jointly encoding an input signal into a set of at least one symbol that spans a chip; 
modulating means for modulating the set of at least one symbol onto a carrier wave; 
spreading means having an input coupled to an output of the encoding means and the modulating means for spreading the set of at least one symbol according to a series of spreading codes; 
a plurality of M wireless transmission means for transmitting the set of at least one symbol over a multi-path wireless channel; and 
processing means having an input coupled to a wireless feedback channel and an output coupled to at least one of the encoding means and the modulating means, said processing means responsive to a channel quality feedback to cause at least one of the encoding means to change an encoding rate and the modulating means to change a modulation.
